    "body": "### Problem\n\n```lua\r\nvim.diagnostic.open_float({scope=\"c\", focus=false, pos={0,0})\r\n```\r\n\r\nAssuming there are diagnostic issues in a file, the code above should open the diagnostic floating window at the top leftmost corner of the nvim window.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, this does not work. The diagnostic window does not open at all.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -u my_issue.lua`\r\n2. `:e foo.lua`\r\n3. edit the file to make a syntax error\r\n4. call `:lua vim.diagnostic.open_float({scope=\"l\", focus=false, pos={0,0}})`\r\n\r\n[nviminimal.zip](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/files/13439517/nviminimal.zip)\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen the `pos` option is present, I expect the diagnostic window to be placed at the row and column specified by the `pos` option\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1588+gdc9f7b814\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
